AUDIO: 'So today is actually our second [music] flight test in a series of three. So the first one we actually flew out in Segovia, Spain. We had a successful [music] flight test out there deploying Hivemind onto the Destinus Hornet. And today we\'re here in Choctaw, Oklahoma. We\'re deploying Hivemind [music] onto a'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hornet alongside the V-Bat. So we\'re going to be executing a number of test cards today with the Hornet using V-Bat [music] as a comms relay. And we\'ll be demonstrating some capabilities that we will eventually deploy onto the Destinus'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] Ruta out in Ukraine. &gt;&gt; The V-Bat is the most advanced aircraft you could ever want. Vertical takeoff and landing, capabilities going up to like 20,000 ft, endurance, takeoff a ship, takeoff a small roof, takeoff'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] from wherever you are. No runways needed. Very, very versatile aircraft. They could do a lot of cool stuff. &gt;&gt; The Hornet is Destinus\'s agile AI-enabled counter-UAS that we\'re using as the proving grounds for the'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'development and the enablement of effectors in the battlefield. &gt;&gt; The Hornet platform by itself has its own [music] autopilot and control system, but it doesn\'t have the intelligence to provide the coordination between [music] agents. And that\'s where'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hivemind really comes in. You have Hivemind working to provide things [music] like the coordinated timing, formation flight, arriving at the target at the same time, you know, tracking those [music] updates on that target location that we\'re being fed through from other Hivemind platforms, whether'

[01:44] [scene:talk]
